      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, a dripping faucet, a common nuisance indeed! You might need a wrench, a screwdriver, and some plumber's tape. First, you'll want to shut off the water supply to the faucet. Then, remove the handle by unscrewing it with the screwdriver. Behind the handle, you'll find the compression nut. Use the wrench to loosen and remove it. The next step is to remove the old washer and replace it with a new one. Don't forget to apply some plumber's tape to the threads before reassembling. Finally, put everything back together and turn the water supply back on. Your faucet should be dripping-free, much like a well-rested goblin after a good night's sleep!",
