    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the dreaded stuck stem, a common challenge for even the most seasoned of plumbers. Fear not, for there is a trick to this, a little bit of wizardry if you will. First, try to wiggle the stem gently with the wrench. Sometimes, a little back-and-forth motion can loosen things up. If that doesn't work, you can try using some penetrating oil. Apply it around the stem and let it sit for a few minutes. This will help to break down any mineral buildup or corrosion that's causing the stem to stick. After that, try wiggling the stem again. If it's still stuck, you might need to use a pair of pliers to gently rock the stem back and forth. Be careful not to apply too much force, or you might indeed snap something. Patience and a gentle touch will be your best allies in this endeavor. Remember, even the most stubborn of goblins can be tamed with the right approach and a bit of persistence. Good luck!",
